{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ListModelRef"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each object in the list may also report changes in itself via some","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"mechanism (normally the [signal[Object](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/object\/onnotify(flags:handler:)] signal).  Taken"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"together with the [signal[ListModel](\/\/documentation\/gio\/listmodel\/onitemschanged(flags:handler:)] signal, this provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for a list that can change its membership, and in which the members can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"change their individual properties.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A good example would be the list of visible wireless network access","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"points, where each access point can report dynamic properties such as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"signal strength.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is important to note that the "},{"code":"GListModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" itself does not report"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changes to the individual items.  It only reports changes to the list","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"membership.  If you want to observe changes to the objects themselves"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then you need to connect signals to the objects that you are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"interested in.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All items in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GListModel"},{"type":"text","text":" are of (or derived from) the same type."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ListModel.get_item_type"},{"type":"text","text":"] returns that type.  The type may be an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"interface, in which case all objects in the list must implement it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The semantics are close to that of an array:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ListModel.get_n_items"},{"type":"text","text":"] returns the number of items in the list"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ListModel.get_item"},{"type":"text","text":"] returns an item at a (0-based) position."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"In order to allow implementations to calculate the list length lazily,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"you can also iterate over items: starting from 0, repeatedly call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ListModel.get_item"},{"type":"text","text":"] until it returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An implementation may create objects lazily, but must take care to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return the same object for a given position until all references to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it are gone."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On the other side, a consumer is expected only to hold references on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"objects that are currently ‘user visible’, in order to facilitate the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"maximum level of laziness in the implementation of the list and to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reduce the required number of signal connections at a given time."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This interface is intended only to be used from a single thread.  The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"thread in which it is appropriate to use it depends on the particular","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementation, but typically it will be from the thread that owns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the thread-default main context (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]) in effect at the time that the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"model was created.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Over time, it has established itself as good practice for list model"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"implementations to provide properties ","type":"text"},{"code":"item-type","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"n-items"},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ease working with them. While it is not required, it is recommended"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that implementations provide these two properties. They should return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the values of [method"},{"code":"Gio.ListModel.get_item_type","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ListModel.get_n_items"},{"text":"] respectively and be defined as such:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["properties[PROP_ITEM_TYPE] =","  g_param_spec_gtype (\"item-type\", NULL, NULL, G_TYPE_OBJECT,","                      G_PARAM_CONSTRUCT_ONLY | G_PARAM_READWRITE | G_PARAM_STATIC_STRINGS);","properties[PROP_N_ITEMS] =","  g_param_spec_uint (\"n-items\", NULL, NULL, 0, G_MAXUINT, 0,","                     G_PARAM_READABLE | G_PARAM_STATIC_STRINGS);"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GListModel"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef","isActive":true},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"GListModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModel"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"code":"GListModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef"},"abstract":[{"code":"GListModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface that represents a mutable list of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[class[Object](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/object]. Its main intention is as a model for various widgets"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in user interfaces, such as list views, but it can also be used as a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"convenient method of returning lists of data, with support for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"updates."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/listmodelref"]}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(_:)-1tm1q","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(_:)-2slyt","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(_:)-854sg","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(_:)-m431","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(_:)-sti1","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"]},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/ptr"],"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/ListModelProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ListModelRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","do